The Mangaung metro tactical response team has arrested three men for alleged possession of boxes of antiretrovirals used to treat HIV. Lt-Col Thabo Covane said the men were nabbed at a mall in Kenneth Kaunda Road, Helicon Heights, in Bloemfontein, on Wednesday. The different brands of ARVs are valued at R85,000. According to a preliminary investigation, the medicines were stolen during a break-in at a clinic in Boshof. The three suspects, aged 28, 43 and 52, will appear in the Bloemfontein magistrate's court soon. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to theÂ Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.